# Credit Card Fraud Detection

## Overview
This project detects fraudulent credit card transactions using machine learning.
The dataset is highly imbalanced (~0.17% fraud), making it a challenging classification problem.
Class imbalance is handled using SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique).

## Dataset
- **Source** [Kaggle – Credit Card Fraud Detection](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud)
- Download the dataset and place `creditcard.csv` in the project directory
- 284,807 transactions
- 492 fraud cases (~0.17%)
- All features are numerical (PCA-transformed)

## Preprocessing
- Train-test split (80/20) with stratification
- Class imbalance handled using **SMOTE** (sampling_strategy=0.1)
- Feature standardization applied

## Models
Three models were trained and compared:

| Model | Description 
| XGBoost | Gradient boosting with early stopping and regularization |
| LightGBM | Fast gradient boosting, efficient on large datasets |
| Random Forest | Ensemble of decision trees, robust to overfitting |

## Results  
| XGBoost ROC AUC- 0.9865 
          precision    recall  f1-score   support
Normal       1.00      1.00      1.00     56864
Fraud        0.54      0.89      0.67        98
| LightGBM ROC AUC- 0.9835 
          precision    recall  f1-score   support
Normal       1.00      1.00      1.00     56864
Fraud        0.81      0.86      0.83        98
| Random Forest ROC AUC- 0.9865 
          precision    recall  f1-score   support
Normal       1.00      1.00      1.00     56864
Fraud        0.54      0.89      0.67        98

> LightGBM achieved the best balance between Precision and Recall for fraud detection, but ROC AUC is a bit more in XGBoost and Random Forest

## Installation
```bash
pip install xgboost lightgbm scikit-learn imbalanced-learn pandas numpy
```